        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 25 at 6:18PM EDT until June 25 at 7:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>SVRGSP

The National Weather Service in Greenville-Spartanburg has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Union County in the Piedmont of North Carolina...

* Until 715 PM EDT.

* At 617 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles northwest
of Monroe, or near Wesley Chapel, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind
damage to trees and power lines.

* Locations impacted include...
Indian Trail, Wesley Chapel, Waxhaw, Mineral Springs, Stallings,
Weddington, and Monroe.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report damaging winds, hail, or flooding to the National
Weather Service by calling toll free, 1, 800, 2 6 7, 8 1 0 1, or by
posting on our Facebook page, or Tweet it using hashtag nwsgsp. Your
message should describe the event and the specific location where it
occurred.</instruction>
